Toy-maker Fisher-Price is recalling 83 toys, including Big Bird and Elmo, due to lead paint.
This follows a similar move by RC2 Corp.
The issue was detected internally and reported to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
Mattel, Fisher-Price's parent company, apologized for the recall, which will impact their operating income.
Concerns over Chinese-made products have parents worried.
Legislation may require more testing of children's products.
The recall highlights the challenges of overseeing production in China.
Consumer advocates are calling for stricter safety measures.
The toy industry faces scrutiny as recalls continue.
